
docker ps -a--both runing and exited containers
docker ps -->status of all runing containers
docker compose ps to check status of all containers
docker compose stop to stop all running containers
docker compose start to start all stopped containers
docker compose down to stop and remove all the running containers
docker compose up --detach to create and start all containers
docker compose up --detach <service_name> to create and start the provided service
docker compose exec service_name sh to open shell inside running container
docker container prune -a to clean up any dangling containers(Will remove all the stopped containers)
docker system prune -fa to prune the entire docker system
docker images --locally stored docker images
docker rm container id --to delete the stopped containers
docker rmi--image id---delete an image from local storage
docker build <docker path file> --to build an image from a specified docker file.
docker --version:- gives the version of docker
docker pull <image name>:- pulls images from repository (hub.docker.com)
docker run -it -d image name :- create a container from an image
docker exec -it container-name bash
docker kill- docker kill container name
docker commit containerid username/imagename:- Creates a new image of an edited container on the local system.
docker run --rm -it prakhar1989/static-site:-
removes the container when it exits and the -it flag specifies an interactive terminal which makes it easier to kill the container with Ctrl+C
docker search ubuntu - searches for an image
